# Environment - NEVER COMMIT SECRETS
# This is critical: .env contains API keys, credentials, and sensitive config
# If you accidentally commit .env, revoke all keys immediately:
# 1. Delete keys from cloud provider console
# 2. Run: git filter-branch --force --index-filter "git rm -r --cached --ignore-unmatch .env"
# 3. Regenerate all keys
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.secret
.env.prod
.env.staging
*.secret
*.key
*.pem

